called Swanson's Law, isn't it?

01:03:09.020 --> 01:03:10.020
Something like that.

01:03:10.020 --> 01:03:11.020
Something like that, yeah.

01:03:11.020 --> 01:03:13.420
And this is an all outgrowth of what's called the experience curve.

01:03:13.420 --> 01:03:16.780
If you double the production of something, then the price of manufacturing falls by like

